Take-Home Assignment: Mini Application Workflow Tracker
Thank you for applying for the Junior–Mid Django/React Full-Stack Developer role.

This assignment is designed to test practical Django and React skills. It should take approximately 3–5 hours. Please do not spend more than that.

Goal
Build a small application workflow tracker with a Django backend API and React frontend.

The workflow should be:

Draft → Submitted → Under Review → Need More Information / Approved / Rejected

Backend Requirements
Use Django with Django Ninja.

Create an Application model with:

tracking_number
applicant_name
applicant_email
company_name
application_type
description
status
reviewer_comment
created_at
updated_at
submitted_at
reviewed_at
Application types:

Recordation
Renewal
Change of Ownership
Change of Name
Discontinuation
Statuses:

Draft
Submitted
Under Review
Need More Information
Approved
Rejected
Create API endpoints for:

Create application draft
List applications
View application details
Update draft application
Submit application
Start review
Record reviewer decision
Workflow rules:

Only Draft applications can be edited.
Only Draft applications can be submitted.
Only Submitted applications can move to Under Review.
Only Under Review applications can receive a reviewer decision.
Approved and Rejected applications cannot be edited.
Need More Information applications can be edited and resubmitted.
Reviewer decision must include a comment for Need More Information or Rejected.
Frontend Requirements
Create a React app with:

Application list screen
Create/edit application form
Application detail screen
Reviewer decision form
The list should show:

Tracking number
Applicant name
Company name
Application type
Status
Created date
The detail page should show actions based on status.

For example:

Draft: Edit / Submit
Submitted: Start Review
Under Review: Approve / Need More Information / Reject
Need More Information: Edit / Resubmit
Approved/Rejected: No edit actions
Submission
Please submit:

GitHub repository link
README with setup instructions
Optional screenshots or short walkthrough video
Your README should explain:

How to run the backend
How to run the frontend
How to run migrations
Any assumptions made
What you would improve with more time
We are not looking for a perfect system. We are looking for working code, clear thinking, good structure, and ability to follow requirements.